# Standard Operating Procedures

# {.tabset}

## DEL

#### IFR

| SID | SID Type | Pronounciation | Aircraft | Runways | Climb |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| INDY# | Vectored | INDY | Any | Any | 5000 |
| MAREO# | Vectored | MAREO | Any | Any | 5000 |


**IFR (LOGAN4) Example:**  
Cleared to Miami Intl airport via the INDY departure, radar vectors, then as filed. Maintain 5000, expect FL300 10 minutes after departure. Departure frequency 128.175, squawk 1234.

**IFR squawk code assignment:**  
via Aurora

#### Pre-Departure Clearance
[PDC](/pdc) via CPDLC is available at this airport

Indianapolis International airport is surrounded by class C airspace. Aircraft entering class C airspace VFR require a clearance in accordance 
with [7110.65 Chapter 7, section 9-2](https://www.faa.gov/air_traffic/publications/atpubs/atc_html/chap7_section_8.html).

**VFR Deaprture:**  
Cleared out of the Indianapolis class charlie airspace to the west, maintain VFR at or below 2500 until further advised. Departure frequency 122.8. Squawk 0301.

**VFR Local Pattern Example:**  
Cleared to operate within the  class charlie airspace, pattern altitude 1500, expect right closed traffic runway 14, squawk 0301.

**VFR squawk code assignment:**  
via Aurora

